<signature>
OnMouseDown()
</signature>
<txttag>
CSNONE
</txttag>
OnMouseDown is called when the user has pressed the mouse button while over the [[GUIElement]] or [[Collider]].
This event is sent to all scripts of the [[Collider]] or [[GUIElement]].
CONVERTEXAMPLE
BEGIN EX
	// Loads the level named "SomeLevel" as a response
	// to the user clicking on the object

	function OnMouseDown () {
		Application.LoadLevel ("SomeLevel");
	}
END EX
This function is not called on objects that belong to Ignore Raycast layer.

OnMouseDown can be a co-routine, simply use the yield statement in the function.
This event is sent to all scripts attached to the [[Collider]] or [[GUIElement]].